HEADWORD: Genethlialogy
<hw>Ge*neth`li*al"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>geneqlhalogi`a</grk> astrology; <grk>gene`qlh</grk> birth +
<grk>lo`gos</grk> discourse.]</ety> <def>Divination as to the destinies
of one newly born; the act or art of casting nativities;
astrology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Genethliatic</ent>⟦br⟧
